SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 817
By Stevens
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Graham Simpson,
Tennessee Titans Mr. Football for Division 1-3A.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing a
young man who, having already achieved great success in high school football, will most
certainly continue to shine on the gridiron and excel in all aspects of life during a bright future;
and
WHEREAS, Graham Simpson, recently named 2025 Tennessee Titans Mr. Football for
Division 1-3A, truly enjoyed a historic and record-breaking season as the quarterback for
Martin's Westview High School; and
WHEREAS, he was also named All-West Tennessee Player of the Year for the second
consecutive year after completing nearly 76% of his passes for 3,565 yards and hurling 43
touchdown passes; and
WHEREAS, Graham Simpson led Westview to its first undefeated season since 1970
(14-0) and the 2025 TSSAA Division I-3A football state championship, as the Chargers
overpowered Gatlinburg-Pittman 62-21 to bring home the gold; and
WHEREAS, Graham Simpson completed 12 of 14 passes for 510 yards and six
touchdowns in the first half alone as Westview scored 55 points, a state record; and
WHEREAS, playing with poise and precision, the sophomore phenom continued his
mastery in the second half, ultimately completing 18 of 21 passes for 566 yards and seven
touchdowns and adding 46 rushing yards and another touchdown on the ground; and
WHEREAS, his seven passing touchdowns tied the state championship record and his
566 passing yards established a new record; and
SJR0817
013149
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Graham Simpson's 99-yard bomb to Donteze Joy set the state
championship record for longest touchdown pass; and
WHEREAS, in light of his legendary performance in the title tilt, it comes as no surprise
that Graham Simpson was named the Most Valuable Player of the 2025 Division I-3A
BlueCross Bowl; and
WHEREAS, for his career at Westview, Graham Simpson has amassed 7,700 passing
yards and thrown 100 touchdowns in only two seasons; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, Graham Simpson was named MaxPreps National Freshman of the
Year after leading Westview to a 14-1 record and the state championship game; and
WHEREAS, he completed nearly 76% of his passes for 4,135 yards and threw 57
touchdown passes in 2024; in a game against Covington, he set the state record for most
passing yards in a game with 620 and tossed eight touchdown passes; and
WHEREAS, Graham Simpson is the No. 5-ranked player in Tennessee from the 2028
class and the No. 10-ranked quarterback in the nation; and
WHEREAS, while Mr. Simpson has already received several college scholarship offers
as a sophomore, we are looking forward to his junior season at Westview, during which he will
surely add to his already impressive credentials as one of the best high school athletes this
State has ever produced; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and recognize Graham Simpson,
Tennessee Titans Mr. Football for Division 1-3A, on his historic and record-breaking season as
a quarterback and congratulate him on leading the Westview Chargers to the state
championship.
- 2 - 013149

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
